<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3388] GroovyASTTransformation phase must be SEMANTIC_ANALYSIS or later for usage</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3388</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using local AST transformations, by using a org.codehaus.groovy.transform.GroovyASTTransformation, the phase of the annotation must be SEMANTIC_ANALYSIS or later. However, the type system allows you to pass in phase identifiers earlier than that. The result is that your transformation is not called. There is no error. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;More discussion here: &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nabble.com/how-to-add-ASTTransformation-objects-to-my-project-tp22262310p22278488.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.nabble.com/how-to-add-ASTTransformation-objects-to-my-project-tp22262310p22278488.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think an error should be thrown if someone tries to pass in a phase earlier than semantic analysis. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
